1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,699
(Previously) No matter how many months, how
many years, or for the rest of my life...

2
00:00:04,700 --> 00:00:08,400
I will wait only for
Your Highness... forever.

3
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,699
Since you've seen us, Mother,

4
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:15,700
you should know that His Highness
and I are in love. We love each other.

5
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:17,999
You shouldn't drag the
heavens down to the dirt!

6
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,720
If heaven and earth obstruct us, if the barrier
between commoner and lord stands in our way...

7
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:24,020
I will show you that I'll destroy them all!

8
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:40,500
Your Highness...

9
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:41,800
Father...

10
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:09,000
"The Edge of Horizon"
(Episode 3)

11
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:13,924
Put on your clothes now.

12
00:02:14,884 --> 00:02:16,044
And go back to your room.

13
00:02:19,964 --> 00:02:21,684
I said go! Now!

14
00:02:33,564 --> 00:02:35,084
What did you do to my son?

15
00:02:39,565 --> 00:02:41,324
It's my fault, my own fault.

16
00:02:42,004 --> 00:02:43,904
Please punish only me.

17
00:02:44,404 --> 00:02:47,924
I was kind to you.
I gave you great opportunities.

18
00:02:49,095 --> 00:02:51,532
You got to study at a higher
level than the servants could.

19
00:02:51,692 --> 00:02:53,444
This is how to repay me?

20
00:02:57,452 --> 00:02:58,644
What did I do wrong?

21
00:03:00,164 --> 00:03:01,524
I just love him.

22
00:03:03,477 --> 00:03:05,798
Stop with your smart mouth already!

23
00:03:06,364 --> 00:03:09,844
A servant like you has nothing to lose!

24
00:03:11,103 --> 00:03:14,244
You don't have to worry about
being a part of a scandal.

25
00:03:14,831 --> 00:03:16,203
But my son has to.

26
00:03:16,609 --> 00:03:18,904
We have pride and dignity.

27
00:03:22,684 --> 00:03:25,164
There is no status in love.

28
00:03:25,388 --> 00:03:28,004
It doesn't care about
your origins or genders.

29
00:03:29,202 --> 00:03:31,484
My love has dignity too.

30
00:03:33,660 --> 00:03:36,244
A servant's dignity has no value.

31
00:03:36,644 --> 00:03:38,904
You can't compare it to us.

32
00:03:39,464 --> 00:03:41,084
What did you do to my son?

33
00:03:41,724 --> 00:03:43,125
What were you thinking?

34
00:03:50,704 --> 00:03:52,084
What did you do?

35
00:03:52,895 --> 00:03:55,204
Please don't hurt him, please.

36
00:03:57,114 --> 00:03:59,304
Please don't hurt Phob, Dad.

37
00:04:01,012 --> 00:04:02,013
Let me go.

38
00:04:02,334 --> 00:04:03,604
Go back to your room!

39
00:04:06,319 --> 00:04:07,844
Go! I told you to leave!

40
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:11,584
You need to leave

41
00:04:13,024 --> 00:04:14,524
or I will kill him.

42
00:04:35,847 --> 00:04:38,644
You need to get the hell out of my palace

43
00:04:39,684 --> 00:04:41,364
before I lose control

44
00:04:41,404 --> 00:04:43,484
and get some blood out of your skull.

45
00:04:44,884 --> 00:04:46,924
Don't ever show your face back here again.

46
00:04:47,924 --> 00:04:48,964
Get out!

47
00:05:33,842 --> 00:05:34,843
Dad?

48
00:05:39,652 --> 00:05:41,364
Did you do anything to Phob?

49
00:05:45,066 --> 00:05:47,244
Please tell me that you
didn't do anything to him

50
00:05:47,304 --> 00:05:48,404
after I left.

51
00:05:54,634 --> 00:05:58,044
You didn't hurt him
more than that, did you?

52
00:06:00,047 --> 00:06:01,048
Get up.

53
00:06:01,604 --> 00:06:04,804
Dad, tell me!

54
00:06:06,484 --> 00:06:08,804
Can you please tell me?

55
00:06:10,524 --> 00:06:13,084
Tell me first.

56
00:06:16,764 --> 00:06:18,604
What did you do to him?

57
00:06:25,916 --> 00:06:26,917
Get up.

58
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:37,054
You didn't hurt him, did you?

59
00:06:40,554 --> 00:06:41,764
Please, just tell me.

60
00:06:42,964 --> 00:06:43,965
Please.

61
00:06:55,431 --> 00:06:56,524
I will pretend that

62
00:06:59,906 --> 00:07:01,884
nothing happened tonight,

63
00:07:03,612 --> 00:07:04,804
and so should you.

64
00:07:06,068 --> 00:07:08,244
Nobody can hear about it.

65
00:07:10,114 --> 00:07:13,084
It will be our secret
for the rest of our lives.

66
00:07:13,804 --> 00:07:15,244
What about Phob?

67
00:07:15,388 --> 00:07:16,389
Listen to me.

68
00:07:18,754 --> 00:07:20,244
You are the one and only hope

69
00:07:21,538 --> 00:07:23,724
of our family.

70
00:07:24,290 --> 00:07:25,444
Do you understand me?

71
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:30,444
Understand?

72
00:07:32,508 --> 00:07:33,509
Yes, sir.

73
00:07:34,819 --> 00:07:36,364
Chat is useless.

74
00:07:37,450 --> 00:07:38,844
He is unreliable.

75
00:07:40,031 --> 00:07:41,444
You are the only one

76
00:07:42,426 --> 00:07:44,924
who can take care of our family.

77
00:07:46,122 --> 00:07:47,504
I have no one left.

78
00:07:51,066 --> 00:07:53,684
It would have been better
if you weren't my son.

79
00:07:55,847 --> 00:07:56,848
Dad?

80
00:07:59,364 --> 00:08:00,365
But you…

81
00:08:01,084 --> 00:08:04,324
are Mom Chao Tinnakorn Varakulvatin.

82
00:08:05,664 --> 00:08:07,844
You were born to be a prince

83
00:08:08,644 --> 00:08:10,924
and you can't change this fact.

84
00:08:18,826 --> 00:08:19,925
I'm sorry.

85
00:08:22,906 --> 00:08:25,804
I don't want to hurt
your feeling like this.

86
00:08:31,642 --> 00:08:33,004
I love you.

87
00:08:36,844 --> 00:08:38,764
You understand me, don't you?

88
00:09:32,815 --> 00:09:34,084
Tin! Tin! Tin!

89
00:09:35,596 --> 00:09:38,044
What happened last night?
Why did Phob come back?

90
00:09:38,279 --> 00:09:39,639
Why? Why was he here?

91
00:09:39,698 --> 00:09:42,404
What? Phob was here last night?

92
00:09:42,484 --> 00:09:44,085
Where is he now?

93
00:09:44,444 --> 00:09:45,445
Dad?

94
00:09:45,924 --> 00:09:48,604
What happened last night?
What troubles did Phob bring?

95
00:09:55,313 --> 00:09:57,110
That name is forbidden in this house.

96
00:09:57,788 --> 00:09:59,644
You can't ask me about it again.

97
00:10:27,842 --> 00:10:30,076
I don't care if it will
be months, or years,

98
00:10:30,439 --> 00:10:31,444
or all my life,

99
00:10:32,508 --> 00:10:34,724
I will wait for you and you only.

100
00:10:36,748 --> 00:10:38,764
No matter what,

101
00:10:39,644 --> 00:10:40,645
I will forever

102
00:10:41,645 --> 00:10:42,646
be your Phob.

103
00:10:45,284 --> 00:10:47,964
It would have been better
if you weren't my son.

104
00:10:48,404 --> 00:10:49,524
But you…

105
00:10:50,364 --> 00:10:53,524
are Mom Chao Tinnakorn Varakulvatin.

106
00:10:54,628 --> 00:10:56,844
You were born to be a prince

107
00:10:57,717 --> 00:10:59,897
and you can't change that fact.

108
00:11:04,180 --> 00:11:07,084
I don't want to hurt
your feeling like this.

109
00:11:08,284 --> 00:11:09,564
I love you.

110
00:11:13,631 --> 00:11:15,404
You understand me, don't you?

111
00:11:37,434 --> 00:11:38,764
Give it to me.

112
00:11:52,644 --> 00:11:54,244
Phob, is it okay?

113
00:12:02,852 --> 00:12:03,853
What about these two?

114
00:12:42,804 --> 00:12:45,604
Hurry up, guys. Come on.

115
00:12:47,274 --> 00:12:48,275
Don't drop it.

116
00:12:48,564 --> 00:12:49,565
Bring them to the car.

117
00:12:49,871 --> 00:12:50,872
Hurry up.

118
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:05,584
Tin,

119
00:13:08,028 --> 00:13:10,092
I hope you know how to behave properly

120
00:13:10,699 --> 00:13:11,724
from now on.

121
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:24,204
Focus on your studies

122
00:13:25,927 --> 00:13:28,683
and forget everything.

123
00:13:29,762 --> 00:13:31,204
Can you promise me that?

124
00:13:34,078 --> 00:13:35,079
Yes, sir.

125
00:13:36,324 --> 00:13:37,604
I know well that...

126
00:13:38,437 --> 00:13:39,957
I'm not just a guy named Tinnakorn

127
00:13:41,446 --> 00:13:43,844
but I am everything to Varakulvatin.

128
00:13:50,524 --> 00:13:51,525
Thank you, son.

129
00:13:54,335 --> 00:13:55,336
Thank you so much.

130
00:14:12,535 --> 00:14:13,536
You should go.

131
00:14:17,996 --> 00:14:19,284
Please take care of it for me.

132
00:15:05,879 --> 00:15:06,880
Dear Phob,

133
00:15:08,615 --> 00:15:11,724
I've been thinking a lot
whether I should write this letter.

134
00:15:14,335 --> 00:15:17,404
And I'm not sure
how you would feel after reading this.

135
00:15:19,300 --> 00:15:21,044
What happened between us

136
00:15:22,186 --> 00:15:23,404
is entirely my fault.

137
00:15:25,304 --> 00:15:28,143
It could be the fact
that we grew up together

138
00:15:29,788 --> 00:15:31,004
and we were so close that

139
00:15:31,895 --> 00:15:35,284
we misunderstood our bond as love.

140
00:15:37,290 --> 00:15:39,084
When I finally came to my senses,

141
00:15:40,282 --> 00:15:41,926
I realized that what happened between us

142
00:15:42,407 --> 00:15:45,124
was just a kid's foolishness
who didn't know anything better.

143
00:15:47,074 --> 00:15:48,924
We should forget everything

144
00:15:49,644 --> 00:15:51,454
and leave it as it should be

145
00:15:52,311 --> 00:15:54,044
for everyone's benefit,

146
00:15:54,724 --> 00:15:56,044
especially for you.

147
00:15:57,944 --> 00:16:00,964
I don't want your future to
be tainted because of this.

148
00:16:04,087 --> 00:16:05,324
From now on,

149
00:16:06,706 --> 00:16:09,324
I will try my best to fulfill my duties,

150
00:16:10,498 --> 00:16:13,624
and I want you to live your life
the way you're meant to.

151
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:18,204
Please forget about me.

152
00:16:19,555 --> 00:16:20,684
Best regards, Tinnakorn,

153
00:16:22,764 --> 00:16:24,044
your old pal.

154
00:17:00,778 --> 00:17:01,904
[Will people gain freedom
or simply changing new boss?]

155
00:17:01,914 --> 00:17:03,740
[Officials need to stay strong,
be struggle like the citizens. ]

156
00:17:03,764 --> 00:17:04,924
[11 Years Later]

157
00:17:05,884 --> 00:17:08,524
[1931, Siam]

158
00:17:33,903 --> 00:17:36,184
The party is turned out to
be spectacular, Your Highness.

159
00:17:36,522 --> 00:17:38,402
It was because you were
helping to organize it,

160
00:17:38,704 --> 00:17:40,524
that's why it went smoothly like this.

161
00:17:41,527 --> 00:17:43,724
Our economy is in bad shape right now

162
00:17:44,341 --> 00:17:49,442
but we organized such a big event. The
newspaper could attack on us tomorrow.

163
00:17:50,904 --> 00:17:52,644
The leftists are criticizing everything

164
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:54,640
and they are getting worse day by day.

165
00:17:55,519 --> 00:17:57,444
Some of them are asking for regime change.

166
00:18:00,135 --> 00:18:01,304
How could it be transformed?

167
00:18:01,959 --> 00:18:04,086
Our country is nothing
like the western countries.

168
00:18:04,380 --> 00:18:05,804
Please don't mind them.

169
00:18:08,084 --> 00:18:10,524
Ms. Siri, please follow me this way.

170
00:18:12,084 --> 00:18:13,085
This way, please.

171
00:18:20,348 --> 00:18:21,349
Oh my,

172
00:18:22,564 --> 00:18:24,304
did you see that solider?

173
00:18:25,484 --> 00:18:28,204
The good-looking one?

174
00:18:28,535 --> 00:18:30,924
I heard that he was a
scholar, studied in France.

175
00:18:32,370 --> 00:18:33,371
He's so handsome.

176
00:19:43,164 --> 00:19:45,684
You and Captain Phobthee know each other?

177
00:19:47,727 --> 00:19:48,728
Captain?

178
00:19:50,204 --> 00:19:51,205
Captain Phobthee

179
00:19:52,564 --> 00:19:54,684
this is Prince Tinnakorn Varakulvatin.

180
00:19:55,023 --> 00:19:56,943
He is His Majesty's
Principal Private Secretary.

181
00:19:57,882 --> 00:19:58,883
Your Highness,

182
00:19:59,972 --> 00:20:01,884
this is Captain Phobthee Munkongphak,

183
00:20:03,655 --> 00:20:05,575
a representative from
army's Artillery Division.

184
00:20:10,060 --> 00:20:11,446
Nice to meet you,

185
00:20:12,780 --> 00:20:13,781
Prince Tinnakorn.

186
00:20:15,687 --> 00:20:16,688
You too.

187
00:20:17,212 --> 00:20:18,604
It's nice to meet you.

188
00:20:20,698 --> 00:20:23,564
Captain Phobthee was a
scholarship student to study in France.

189
00:20:24,356 --> 00:20:26,404
He was the top student of his class.

190
00:20:26,904 --> 00:20:28,424
He has a bright future ahead for sure.

191
00:20:34,690 --> 00:20:36,204
I am just a son of commoners.

192
00:20:39,866 --> 00:20:41,524
But someone once taught me that

193
00:20:43,482 --> 00:20:46,726
people should live their lives
the way they're meant to.

194
00:20:49,604 --> 00:20:50,884
That's why I was trying so hard,

195
00:20:51,605 --> 00:20:53,644
and striving to be where I am today.

196
00:20:59,804 --> 00:21:00,904
Excuse me,

197
00:21:03,004 --> 00:21:04,005
Your Highness.

198
00:22:12,204 --> 00:22:13,724
I wondered where you were.

199
00:22:14,124 --> 00:22:16,244
- To get your favorite drink.
- Thank you. Cheers.

200
00:22:22,786 --> 00:22:23,787
Refreshing.

201
00:22:26,252 --> 00:22:27,964
- You're right.
- Nice smell too.

202
00:22:35,602 --> 00:22:37,084
Who is he?

203
00:22:37,644 --> 00:22:38,645
Your friend?

204
00:22:40,076 --> 00:22:41,444
No, he's not.

205
00:22:42,050 --> 00:22:44,051
He's not someone that I know.

206
00:22:45,924 --> 00:22:47,684
We should go inside.

207
00:22:57,055 --> 00:22:58,524
Our country is in distress,

208
00:22:59,114 --> 00:23:01,844
but a fundraising event is
pretentiously extravagant.

209
00:23:02,284 --> 00:23:03,604
This is ridiculous.

210
00:23:03,810 --> 00:23:06,204
When I wrote about it in the newspaper,

211
00:23:06,364 --> 00:23:07,764
they thought that I was sarcastic.

212
00:23:10,037 --> 00:23:14,484
This is the first time that I met
Prince Tinnakorn, the royal secretary.

213
00:23:15,220 --> 00:23:17,004
He is so good-looking

214
00:23:17,215 --> 00:23:19,444
just like people have said.

215
00:23:20,954 --> 00:23:24,524
He seems to be the perfect match
for his fiancée, named…

216
00:23:26,484 --> 00:23:27,524
What is her name?

217
00:23:30,775 --> 00:23:31,776
Ruethaisiri.

218
00:23:37,351 --> 00:23:39,471
You lived in Varakulvatin Palace
when you were a kid.

219
00:23:40,818 --> 00:23:42,538
How was Prince Tinnakorn when he was young?

220
00:23:43,164 --> 00:23:45,165
Has he always been this good-looking?

221
00:24:06,724 --> 00:24:08,644
- What do you think?
- I'll keep going.

222
00:24:10,804 --> 00:24:12,124
- Come to me.
- Wait.

223
00:24:13,124 --> 00:24:14,125
It's straight for me.

224
00:24:20,276 --> 00:24:21,324
It's not fun anymore.

225
00:24:27,332 --> 00:24:29,164
Where are you rushing to, sir?

226
00:24:29,396 --> 00:24:32,244
- But I…
- Well, you're Prince Chatthorn,

227
00:24:32,604 --> 00:24:35,644
we can loan you some money,
just give me the number.

228
00:24:36,228 --> 00:24:37,444
Come on, let's continue.

229
00:24:37,909 --> 00:24:38,910
This way, sir.

230
00:24:39,199 --> 00:24:40,964
Come on, follow me.

231
00:24:44,506 --> 00:24:45,764
Have a seat, sir.

232
00:24:49,836 --> 00:24:51,404
Take care of him, okay.

233
00:24:52,231 --> 00:24:54,324
Enjoy yourself.

234
00:24:57,684 --> 00:25:00,124
- Let's continue.
- Go on!

235
00:25:04,404 --> 00:25:05,484
So sweet.

236
00:25:10,617 --> 00:25:12,203
[You only serve the royalty, getting rid of the commoners]

237
00:25:12,476 --> 00:25:14,904
Not fair to us!

238
00:25:22,804 --> 00:25:23,805
This is not fair!

239
00:25:24,138 --> 00:25:26,578
We've been working for the government
for more than 10 years.

240
00:25:26,828 --> 00:25:29,484
And now you're firing us
to maintain the balance?

241
00:25:29,522 --> 00:25:33,004
- Not fair!
- [Siam will be doomed because of trashy noblemen!]

242
00:25:33,596 --> 00:25:35,084
Siam will be in big trouble for sure.

243
00:25:35,826 --> 00:25:37,724
Not fair!

244
00:25:54,764 --> 00:25:57,046
Phob! You little servant!

245
00:25:57,778 --> 00:25:59,164
You!

246
00:26:04,524 --> 00:26:06,044
I am Captain Phobtheee

247
00:26:06,610 --> 00:26:08,244
from the Artillery Division.

248
00:26:08,884 --> 00:26:11,255
I am representing the division
and I'm here to ask for clarity

249
00:26:11,279 --> 00:26:13,764
about pension payments
for junior rank soldiers.

250
00:26:14,964 --> 00:26:16,444
Captain? Really?

251
00:26:17,124 --> 00:26:20,204
I've never thought that
you could push yourself to this level.

252
00:26:23,239 --> 00:26:24,844
I've never thought either that

253
00:26:26,284 --> 00:26:28,644
a person who kept failing classes like you

254
00:26:29,730 --> 00:26:32,690
would be working as the assistant to the
director-general of the finance ministry.

255
00:26:34,866 --> 00:26:35,867
No wonder why

256
00:26:36,626 --> 00:26:38,244
- there're problems in the budget.
- Phob!

257
00:26:40,887 --> 00:26:43,924
Don't you ever think that
just because you're a soldier

258
00:26:44,092 --> 00:26:45,652
and you can be at the same level as me.

259
00:26:47,364 --> 00:26:49,764
You must have been trying so hard

260
00:26:50,063 --> 00:26:51,244
to become who you are now.

261
00:26:51,844 --> 00:26:54,511
Still, you're just a servant to me.

262
00:26:56,484 --> 00:26:57,764
You're so right.

263
00:26:58,666 --> 00:27:00,134
I've been trying so hard to be here.

264
00:27:01,364 --> 00:27:02,404
Unlike someone

265
00:27:03,104 --> 00:27:05,684
- who needs his daddy's favoritism.
- Phob!

266
00:27:12,385 --> 00:27:13,724
Long time no see.

267
00:27:15,424 --> 00:27:17,084
You're so bold,

268
00:27:17,884 --> 00:27:19,284
Captain Phobthee.

269
00:27:21,801 --> 00:27:24,324
Time changes, people change, sir.

270
00:27:25,700 --> 00:27:26,844
I hope that next time

271
00:27:27,663 --> 00:27:29,804
you will finish the reimbursement matter

272
00:27:30,068 --> 00:27:31,504
that hasn't been paid for months.

273
00:27:40,015 --> 00:27:41,016
Right,

274
00:27:44,170 --> 00:27:46,630
please send my regards to Prince Tinnakorn.

275
00:27:48,719 --> 00:27:50,799
We met the other night at the party.
We were so busy

276
00:27:51,802 --> 00:27:53,882
that we didn't have a
chance to chat about our past.

277
00:28:09,274 --> 00:28:11,484
Didn't you see his eyes
when he looked at me?

278
00:28:11,684 --> 00:28:13,804
How that low-rank soldier looked at me?

279
00:28:13,911 --> 00:28:15,964
He accused you of helping me with the job.

280
00:28:16,044 --> 00:28:18,045
What's wrong?

281
00:28:18,104 --> 00:28:19,644
- Why are you yelling?
- Grandma.

282
00:28:19,682 --> 00:28:21,564
- It's about Phob.
- Why?

283
00:28:21,597 --> 00:28:23,077
He is now a captain in the military.

284
00:28:23,970 --> 00:28:27,084
- What? Good for him.
- Grandma!

285
00:28:27,287 --> 00:28:28,288
Don't compliment him.

286
00:28:28,418 --> 00:28:30,244
- What?
- He's so arrogant.

287
00:28:30,267 --> 00:28:31,907
He keeps on showing off his title around.

288
00:28:32,100 --> 00:28:34,304
He didin't show any respect to both of us.

289
00:28:34,324 --> 00:28:35,884
Hey! Stop whining already.

290
00:28:36,986 --> 00:28:39,570
You need to take care of
the soldiers' reimbursement

291
00:28:39,989 --> 00:28:42,917
so he couldn't drag you
into a mess, so embarrassing.

292
00:28:46,890 --> 00:28:47,891
Yes, sir.

293
00:29:09,532 --> 00:29:10,533
Tin.

294
00:29:12,124 --> 00:29:13,125
Yeah?

295
00:29:14,682 --> 00:29:15,683
We need to talk.

296
00:29:21,924 --> 00:29:23,524
You met Phob, didn't he?

297
00:29:25,421 --> 00:29:27,717
Yes, at the party.

298
00:29:30,118 --> 00:29:31,644
But you can tust me.

299
00:29:32,324 --> 00:29:33,644
I won't cause any trouble.

300
00:29:36,904 --> 00:29:38,244
Of course, I trust you.

301
00:29:39,140 --> 00:29:41,684
I know that you know
what is right and wrong.

302
00:29:43,324 --> 00:29:44,844
It's somebody else that I don't trust.

303
00:29:46,599 --> 00:29:47,804
If you're talking about Phob,

304
00:29:49,378 --> 00:29:50,724
don't worry about him.

305
00:29:52,772 --> 00:29:54,004
He must have hated me already.

306
00:29:55,540 --> 00:29:57,124
What happened between me and Phob

307
00:29:58,136 --> 00:29:59,404
ended that night already.

308
00:30:36,807 --> 00:30:37,808
I love you.

309
00:30:41,068 --> 00:30:42,324
I love you, too.

310
00:31:11,188 --> 00:31:12,444
If you're talking about Phob,

311
00:31:15,204 --> 00:31:16,564
don't worry about him.

312
00:31:17,594 --> 00:31:18,844
He must have hated me already.

313
00:31:19,802 --> 00:31:21,264
What happened between me and Phob

314
00:31:21,380 --> 00:31:22,764
ended that night already.

315
00:31:27,284 --> 00:31:28,324
That night?

316
00:31:30,952 --> 00:31:33,397
It must be the night
that Phob came to see Tin.

317
00:31:35,764 --> 00:31:36,765
Is that…

318
00:31:37,236 --> 00:31:38,237
Phob?

319
00:31:39,564 --> 00:31:41,204
What happened that night?

320
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:51,604
What did the students from France who came
back at the same time as you say about this?

321
00:31:52,802 --> 00:31:54,524
They agreed that if we don't do something,

322
00:31:55,484 --> 00:31:57,724
the people will struggle more.

323
00:31:59,908 --> 00:32:01,324
We need to follow our plan

324
00:32:01,882 --> 00:32:03,362
like we discussed when we were there.

325
00:32:06,916 --> 00:32:10,124
The noble people are living
their lives if nothing happens

326
00:32:10,604 --> 00:32:12,044
when people are in crisis like this.

327
00:32:13,164 --> 00:32:14,964
People start to question
about the government

328
00:32:15,452 --> 00:32:18,364
asking who are they ruling for?

329
00:32:21,399 --> 00:32:23,924
I will write a piece about
people's dissatisfaction,

330
00:32:24,154 --> 00:32:26,484
that they're done with being
taken advantage of like this.

331
00:32:26,768 --> 00:32:28,397
You need to be careful.

332
00:32:29,316 --> 00:32:32,004
There are people who will not be
pleased with your work, Janthorn.

333
00:32:34,204 --> 00:32:35,564
If they are not pleased,

334
00:32:36,124 --> 00:32:38,484
it means that they are
taking advantage of people.

335
00:32:40,220 --> 00:32:42,244
Just like what you are doing now.

336
00:32:43,154 --> 00:32:44,604
People who disagree with my piece

337
00:32:45,159 --> 00:32:46,804
are someone who lose benefits from it.

338
00:32:48,972 --> 00:32:50,844
We need to be careful.

339
00:32:51,351 --> 00:32:52,444
I heard that

340
00:32:52,956 --> 00:32:54,870
the royal family members and noble people

341
00:32:56,412 --> 00:32:58,004
are watching progressives closely.

342
00:32:58,903 --> 00:33:01,004
I heard the same rumor as you.

343
00:33:01,278 --> 00:33:04,910
I also heard that they wore a
blue mark as their symbol.

344
00:33:10,215 --> 00:33:11,404
Blue mark?

345
00:33:37,207 --> 00:33:38,208
What did you say?

346
00:33:38,962 --> 00:33:40,884
Some people who are working
for the Lok Siam newspaper

347
00:33:40,904 --> 00:33:43,004
were a part of the rebels
from the 1912 Palace Revolt?

348
00:33:43,527 --> 00:33:45,324
I just heard about it also.

349
00:33:45,815 --> 00:33:48,484
That's why they keep on
attacking the government.

350
00:33:52,583 --> 00:33:55,404
Our late King was so kind
and didn't order to execute them.

351
00:33:56,055 --> 00:33:58,304
And they didn't show
their gratitude at all.

352
00:33:58,642 --> 00:34:00,562
Instead, they are
seeking regime change.

353
00:34:00,759 --> 00:34:02,684
They are so ungratful to their own country.

354
00:34:02,823 --> 00:34:04,484
And they are working everywhere;

355
00:34:04,706 --> 00:34:07,284
we need to keep an eye on them.

356
00:34:07,959 --> 00:34:09,884
I feel so relieved when I visit ministries

357
00:34:10,023 --> 00:34:12,604
and see people who are
wearing the blue mark, our symbol,

358
00:34:12,684 --> 00:34:14,164
to help observe the opposite side.

359
00:34:19,084 --> 00:34:21,644
We need to protect
our nation's main pillar,

360
00:34:21,888 --> 00:34:23,684
nobody can destroy it.

361
00:34:32,231 --> 00:34:33,244
The upcoming celebration

362
00:34:33,559 --> 00:34:35,964
is the significant event of the nation.

363
00:34:36,370 --> 00:34:37,676
I wish all parties

364
00:34:37,890 --> 00:34:40,164
to work on it carefully.

365
00:34:41,751 --> 00:34:44,194
Mr. Secretary, if we're all ready,

366
00:34:44,412 --> 00:34:46,413
please start with the meeting agenda now.

367
00:35:03,844 --> 00:35:06,924
I am Captain Phobtheee
from the Artillery Division.

368
00:35:07,604 --> 00:35:10,084
I was assigned to be in
charge of arranging soldiers

369
00:35:10,431 --> 00:35:11,924
and security team for

370
00:35:12,260 --> 00:35:15,304
the 150th Anniversary of
Rattanakosin's celebration.

371
00:35:15,783 --> 00:35:18,823
Right, are you working for Mr. Kitti?

372
00:35:19,918 --> 00:35:22,404
I've heard a lot about you.

373
00:35:22,876 --> 00:35:24,164
About your job,

374
00:35:24,418 --> 00:35:26,916
I'd like to assign Mr. Secretary

375
00:35:27,567 --> 00:35:31,644
to coordinate with you directly.

376
00:35:33,204 --> 00:35:34,205
Please have a seat.

377
00:35:36,479 --> 00:35:39,204
Mr. Secretary, please start.

378
00:35:44,219 --> 00:35:48,457
I'd like to start with the first agenda
item about our duties and coordination.

379
00:35:48,607 --> 00:35:52,004
It requires all parties
to work together closely.

380
00:36:06,034 --> 00:36:07,035
Hey.

381
00:36:10,444 --> 00:36:11,604
I'm here to remind you that

382
00:36:12,650 --> 00:36:14,964
when you're done with
the minutes of meeting,

383
00:36:15,604 --> 00:36:16,764
please send it to me.

384
00:36:18,681 --> 00:36:19,682
Sure.

385
00:36:20,004 --> 00:36:22,844
When my team is done
with it, I'll send it to you.

386
00:36:27,340 --> 00:36:28,341
Thank you.

387
00:37:27,183 --> 00:37:28,083
Thank you.

388
00:37:47,170 --> 00:37:48,171
Thank you.

389
00:38:05,684 --> 00:38:07,324
You're acting as if I am that disgusting.

390
00:38:11,270 --> 00:38:12,924
I didn't do such thing, Mr. Phobthee.

391
00:38:14,713 --> 00:38:16,004
How could I dislike you?

392
00:38:16,724 --> 00:38:17,804
Look at you now.

393
00:38:20,239 --> 00:38:22,564
You're a soldier with a bright future.

394
00:38:31,364 --> 00:38:32,804
Someone once told me that

395
00:38:34,884 --> 00:38:36,244
people's status

396
00:38:37,066 --> 00:38:38,786
can be different based on their competency.

397
00:38:39,796 --> 00:38:41,004
He also told me that

398
00:38:42,159 --> 00:38:44,324
he believed in me.

399
00:38:47,684 --> 00:38:50,844
That has kept me motivated
and working hard until now.

400
00:38:53,324 --> 00:38:55,844
Your achievements come
from your own ability,

401
00:38:57,094 --> 00:38:59,314
it's not because of nonsense
words of encouragement.

402
00:39:01,503 --> 00:39:02,504
Nonsense?

403
00:39:05,399 --> 00:39:06,400
You're right, I guess.

404
00:39:08,263 --> 00:39:11,324
The speaker may not feel anything.

405
00:39:12,546 --> 00:39:14,724
It's just words full of
lies and meaningless.

406
00:39:17,287 --> 00:39:19,004
Then you should forget about it already.

407
00:39:20,071 --> 00:39:21,964
Don't focus on some
random and useless words.

408
00:39:29,444 --> 00:39:30,644
Can you teach me

409
00:39:31,468 --> 00:39:35,804
how to stop one's feelings, to
be ruthless and cruel like you?

410
00:39:38,644 --> 00:39:40,484
If you're done with the government work,

411
00:39:40,504 --> 00:39:41,784
then I need to ask you to leave.

412
00:39:42,900 --> 00:39:45,084
You're disturbing my work.

413
00:40:29,506 --> 00:40:31,724
I spent all money.

414
00:40:32,727 --> 00:40:33,804
Phob! You!

415
00:40:34,796 --> 00:40:37,396
It's because of you! You stick
your nose where it doesn't belong.

416
00:40:55,772 --> 00:40:57,444
Thank you so much, Sakchai.

417
00:40:58,004 --> 00:40:59,154
No worries.

418
00:40:59,388 --> 00:41:01,764
It is my honor that you
decided to ask me for a loan.

419
00:41:13,504 --> 00:41:15,304
You will get your money back soon.

420
00:41:16,463 --> 00:41:17,964
There is no need to hurry.

421
00:41:18,570 --> 00:41:21,164
We're friends and I will help you.

422
00:41:25,324 --> 00:41:27,004
Thank you so much, Sakchai.

423
00:41:27,615 --> 00:41:28,904
Safe travels, Your Highness.

424
00:41:44,887 --> 00:41:48,404
Thank you for inviting me
to watch the performance.

425
00:41:49,524 --> 00:41:51,644
You can tell me whether you like it.

426
00:41:51,996 --> 00:41:54,876
I need to see if they're the right choice
to perform in the celebration.

427
00:42:04,654 --> 00:42:05,655
Phob!

428
00:42:06,079 --> 00:42:07,564
Tin, Phob is here.

429
00:42:12,470 --> 00:42:13,830
Is this Phob?

430
00:42:13,854 --> 00:42:15,414
Long time no see.

431
00:42:16,444 --> 00:42:19,564
Wow! You're a soldier now?

432
00:42:21,487 --> 00:42:22,488
Yes, Your Highness.

433
00:42:22,804 --> 00:42:24,604
It's nice to see you again.

434
00:42:25,724 --> 00:42:27,164
I miss the old days,

435
00:42:27,266 --> 00:42:30,130
when Phob lived in the same place as you.

436
00:42:30,591 --> 00:42:34,364
I went to visit you and you were
always hanging out with Phob.

437
00:42:42,764 --> 00:42:45,364
You're not going to
introduce this beautiful lady?

438
00:42:45,548 --> 00:42:46,964
I am waiting for a while now.

439
00:42:50,396 --> 00:42:53,164
- Right, she is…
- My name is Janthorn.

440
00:42:53,404 --> 00:42:55,444
I'm a journalist at the Lok Siam newspaper.

441
00:42:55,679 --> 00:42:57,737
It's nice to meet you, Prince Tinnakorn

442
00:42:57,876 --> 00:42:59,204
and M.R. Ruethaisiri.

443
00:43:00,644 --> 00:43:03,324
Nice to meet you, too, Ms. Janthorn.

444
00:43:05,004 --> 00:43:06,338
You asked me to introduce you

445
00:43:06,834 --> 00:43:08,338
and you introduced yourself first?

446
00:43:08,804 --> 00:43:11,324
I can't wait for you any longer.

447
00:43:11,522 --> 00:43:13,764
You're too slow and we
could miss everything.

448
00:43:14,924 --> 00:43:18,164
Hey, I took you here to get
a scoop for the celebration.

449
00:43:18,751 --> 00:43:21,404
Fine, don't ask me to do
anything for you anymore.

450
00:43:23,978 --> 00:43:26,084
What? A sulking soldier?

451
00:44:30,018 --> 00:44:31,019
No garland

452
00:44:32,204 --> 00:44:34,044
but you can have a cotton rose.

453
00:44:44,832 --> 00:44:46,204
So it means that

454
00:44:46,604 --> 00:44:49,924
you choose me. Is that right?

455
00:45:17,740 --> 00:45:19,364
Why didn't you stay to watch the show?

456
00:45:24,010 --> 00:45:25,124
I'm not feeling well.

457
00:45:28,847 --> 00:45:29,848
Are you sure?

458
00:45:32,495 --> 00:45:34,935
It isn't because of the show
reminded you of our past, is it?

459
00:45:35,676 --> 00:45:37,236
That's why you can't stand watching it.

460
00:45:38,434 --> 00:45:40,564
I told you that I forgot all about it.

461
00:45:50,407 --> 00:45:51,408
Let me go.

462
00:45:56,924 --> 00:45:57,925
Hey!

463
00:46:20,300 --> 00:46:23,300
(Next Episode) Have you and Phob
talked about anything other than work?

464
00:46:23,800 --> 00:46:27,299
No matter what, you must not fall for him.
We still need information from Thin.

465
00:46:27,300 --> 00:46:29,300
Stop! Phob, stop!

466
00:46:32,300 --> 00:46:35,099
What's between you two
is completely impossible.

467
00:46:35,100 --> 00:46:37,199
We and His Highness
live in different worlds.

468
00:46:37,200 --> 00:46:39,300
It might not be like that forever, Mother.

469
00:46:43,500 --> 00:46:46,500
To Your Highness, the
past is probably worthless.

470
00:46:46,800 --> 00:46:48,500
Your Highness should just forget about it.

471
00:46:48,900 --> 00:46:49,900
Let me go.

472
00:46:51,100 --> 00:46:52,699
If Your Highness wants me to let go...

473
00:46:52,700 --> 00:46:54,500
Your Highness should be firmer than this.
